Is AUTHOR wrong in the post ? POST : I want to start off by saying I think it's great that they're doing that but I feel like people advocate so hard for depression and anxiety because those people can be "fixed". People with Bipolar, BPD, DID, Schizo, ect just get like... pushed to the side even though people are like "We're mental health advocates." No one's mind EVER jumps to that. It's always 'suicide, depression and anxiety' awareness. 

&amp;#x200B;

I can't even talk about the medications I take at my job without receiving "hushing" and/or dirty looks from my co-workers but if someone is having an anxiety attack they're treated totally different. Is this just a me thing, AITA??
